course.subject: SOSC
course.name: Research Pro-seminar
course.description: This course is intended for students to share and develop ideas for the purpose of the prospective Capstone Project. Students will present and discuss their progression during regular sessions. Faculty with access to candidate datasets will be invited to hold information sessions for students. Some class sessions will also feature speakers in the Division of Social Science seminar series. For QSA students in their fourth year of study only. Graded P or F. Instructor's approval is required for enrolling in the course.
